The paper discusses a redundancy management mechanism for Peer-to-Peer backup applications, which involves data durability rather than availability. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves network communication and simulations, which could place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses practical issues and solutions, which could suggest a focus on Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Systems and Control (cs.SY).
